                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A cylindrical liquid scintillator tube of",
                "100 cm in length and 5.3 cm in inner diameter with two",
                "photomultipliers at both ends of the tube. The position",
                "information of the incident neutrons was obtained from",
                "the time difference of both photomultiplier signals."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "MONITOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The neutron beam was monitored by counting associated",
                "alpha's produced in the T(d,n)He-4 reaction"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF",
                "PSD",
                "ASSOP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The associated (alpha-)particle TOF",
                "technique and pulse shape (n-gamma) discrimination",
                "were used to reduce the background.",
                " EN-RSL: The energy resolution of the measuring",
                "system is 1 MeV so the data include contributions",
                "from neutrons scattered inelastically from low-lying",
                "excited levels."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The results were corrected for the neutron flux",
                "attenuation, multiple neutron scattering and finite",
                "geometry by the monte-carlo method."
              ]
            }
          ],
